						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone on the tank bund.</hi></p>						

						<p>Rāmachandra—A.D. 1289.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the king's regnal <hi rend="bold">year 18, Sarvadhāri, Pushya, s11u. 8, Saturday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1289, January 1, Saturday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription records the death, by Jaina rite, of a certain Mādayya, the son of Sāyiseṭṭi and Mādavve, and a disciple of Samantabhadradēva, a Jaina ascetic belonging to Mūla-saṁgha.</p>						

						</summary>
